Three important properties control the space that surrounds each HTML element: Padding, margin, and border

Padding:
controls the amount of space between the element and its border

Margin:
controls the amount of space between an element's border and surrounding elements.
margin-top, margin-right, margin-bottom, margin-left properties

Padding:
Padding of an element on all four sides with padding-top, padding-right, padding-bottom and padding-left properties.
